sp_css.css:
/*
Collection of CSS that is used to style Restricted Group Banner and Restricted Group Badge
STRY0101803 - added assignment group banner Created 2021-05-18
2.7.0 | 2021-08-09 | mmcc | STRY0104884 Badges do not pass 508/WCAG compliance
2.7.0 | 2021-08-10 | mmcc | STRY0104983 - Stretch- Technical Debt - Update CSS to organize into proper hierarchy of CSS
  Put into a style sheet
2.8 | 2022-02-02 | mmcc | STRY0117772 - Tech Debt - Identify Style Sheets when viewed from browser Dev Tools
  Added .RestrictedGroupBannerStyleSheet to name which style sheet this is when viewed from browser Dev Tools
2.8 | 2022-07-19 | mmcc | STRY0118268 - Stretch- Post Fixed Header+Action Bar for Modals- Clean up to display more content on screen 
Change Restricted Group Banner to be a ribbon
*/
.RestrictedGroupBannerStyleSheet { display: none; } /* Name of Style Sheet, do not use to style HTML */


/*
Restricted Group Banner - looks like a rectangle > 2.8 now a ribbon
Tasker's Restricted Group is really a label from ServiceNow's Task table, column named assignment_group
*/
.dtech-restricted-group-banner {
  background-color: $restricted-group-banner-bg;
  color: $restricted-group-banner-text;
  font-size: smaller;
  text-align: center;
}

/*
Restricted Group Badge - looks like a pill
Must have Bootstrap class badge and restricted-group within its class attribute
*/
.restricted-group.badge {
  background-color: $restricted-group-badge-bg;
  color: $restricted-group-badge-text;
}
